Meetings

   29 - 31oct
   High Mountain Summit

   Mountain regions cover about a quarter of the Earth’s land surface and
   are home to a quarter of the world’s population. They are important
   sources of freshwater and centres of biological and cultural diversity.
   Rising global temperatures are causing unprecedented changes and are
   accompanied by an increased risk of disasters.

For more information and registration visit: High Mountain Summit

